For future reference. Reaper and DaVinci Resolve are free programs that offer excellent video editing options.

Technically, Reaper costs $60 so long as you make less than $20,000 a year using the program, but it has a "I'm still evaluating" option prompt every time you open the program that lets you "evaluate" it for free indefinitely.
either one you'd recommend over the other for reasons, dadro? :o

Reaper is primarily an audio editing program that happens to have a happily extensive video editing suite. DR is hyper focused on the video editing part, but in its depths, a newcomer will find themselves very lost.
I obviously prefer Reaper for... obvious reasons. But it's also super nice in that it's very flexible in customization.
But both have great tutorials available for getting into their programs on YouTube.
Nice.  I'm sure I'll have more videos in the future

You probably want to look into DaVinci honestly. I'm an audio guy, so navigating that space is fine for me, but if your focus is on video editing, it'd probably be optimal for you to get into the program ~designed~ for those shenanigans and its workflow.
